    "The following theorem trivially implies Theorem 1.6.L 1 (Q) P d (Q) L ∞ (Q) (P d (Q)) * P d (Q)Theorem 3.18.",
    "The prescribed Jacobian equation has strong Lipschitz non-regularity, if and only if the range of Em * is not closed.",
    "In particular, if the prescribed Jacobian equation has strong Lipschitz non-regularity, then Conjecture 1.1 fails.",
    "By the open mapping theorem, the operator Em * has closed range if and only if it is an isomorphism into P d (Q).",
    "This is the case, if and only if there exists a constant C such that, whenever u n ∈ L 1 (Q) satisfies (i) from Definition 1.3, then ∥Em * (u n)∥ P d ≥ C. (3.5) Indeed, C corresponds to the operator norm of the inverse of Em *."
